	<section class="none" name="About EclipseLink">
		<description>
			<h1>EclipseLink</h1>
			<div style="text-align:justify">
				The
				<b>
					Eclipse Persistence Services Project (EclipseLink)
				</b>
				project's goal is to deliver a comprehensive Java
				persistence framework. EclipseLink will focus on
				providing leading edge support, including advanced
				feature extensions, for the dominant persistence
				standards for each target data source:
				<ul>
					<li>
						<b>JPA</b>
						: Java Persistence API for relational databases
					</li>
					<li>
						<b>MOXy</b>
						: Java API for XML Binding (JAXB)for XML
					</li>
					<li>
						<b>SDO</b>
						: Service Data Objects for SCA
					</li>
					<li>
						<b>DBWS</b>
						: Database Web Services
					</li>
					<li>
						<b>EIS</b>
						: Java Connector Architecture (JCA) for EIS
					</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</description>
	</section>

